<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using substitution.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}-{6}{y}=-{28}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}-{5}{y}=-{20}</m></p>
<p><input type="text" style="width:10.6ch" name="qn0" id="qn0" value="" autocomplete="off" aria-label="Question 1" class="text"/></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{5},{8}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to solve the first equation for <m>\displaystyle{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}+-{6}{y}=-{28}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}=-{28}-{\left(-{6}{y}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{-{28}-{\left(-{6}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{4}}}}</m></p>
<p>Then we can substitute this into the second equation.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{\left(\frac{{-{28}-{\left(-{6}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{4}}}}\right)}+-{5}{y}=-{20}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-\frac{{4}}{{-{{4}}}}\cdot{\left(-{28}\right)}--\frac{{4}}{{-{{4}}}}{\left(-{6}\right)}{y}+-{5}{y}=-{20}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{28}-{\left({6}\right)}{y}+-{5}{y}=-{20}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{6}{y}+{\left(-{5}\right)}{y}=-{20}--{28}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{6}{y}+{\left(-{5}\right)}{y}={8}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\left({6}+{\left(-{5}\right)}\right)}{y}={8}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{1}{y}={8}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=\frac{{8}}{{1}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}={8}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}+-{6}{\left({8}\right)}=-{28}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}+{\left(-{48}\right)}=-{28}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}=-{28}-{\left(-{48}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{4}{x}={20}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{20}}{{-{{4}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-{5}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left(-{5},{8}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
